## Attack-surface matrix (all negative)
| Edge/sigma structural leakage | No plaintext relation |
No practical public-only plaintext recovery was identified. Challenge v2 successfully removes the v1 R_com oracle; the two-layer wrapper with independent masks and fresh Pedersen blindings leaves no public verifiable predicate. All probes this session reproduce the smoke-ui/octra-hfhe-v2-security-assessment negative result. The second-half reward track (writeup to dev@octra.org) is the appropriate claim given no solve was achieved.
